genresAdvancedInfo.name: christian symphonic metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Christian symphonic metal is a subgenre of heavy metal music that combines the aggressive sound of metal with the grandeur and complexity of orchestral music. The lyrics often deal with Christian themes and values, and the music is characterized by its powerful vocals, intricate guitar solos, and epic symphonic arrangements.
